   howTo:"K&R C Programming Language is still the canonical text. Write C programs that read/write files and use dynamic memory. Use Valgrind to catch leaks immediately. Compile with -Wall -Wextra from day one.",
   safety:"Buffer overflow code is instructional — only practice exploitation on systems you own or in authorized lab environments.",
