   roadmap:["basic C program","pointers + malloc/free","linked list/stack/tree in C","debug segfault/leak w/ valgrind","POSIX sockets client/server","threads + mutex + race fix","interpreter/parser","kernel module concept","CVE analysis + lab PoC"],
   advance:[
   "Reach L1: write a C program that reads input, computes, and prints; compile with gcc.",
   "Reach L2: use pointers, pointer arithmetic, and dynamic memory (malloc/free) without leaks.",
   "Reach L3: implement a linked list, stack, and binary tree using struct and pointer manipulation.",
   "Reach L4: use valgrind to find and fix a segfault and a memory leak; explain buffer overflows.",
   "Reach L5: write a POSIX socket client/server echo application.",
   "Reach L6: use pthreads/std::thread with a mutex; identify and fix a race condition.",
   "Reach L7: implement a simple tokenizer and parser for a toy language.",
   "Reach L8: understand and prototype a kernel module or OS-level hook concept.",
   "Reach L9: read a real CVE involving buffer overflow or use-after-free; explain it and write a PoC in an authorized lab."],
