   levels:[
     "Create users and groups; configure file permissions using both chmod octal and symbolic notation; explain setuid/setgid","Install, enable, disable, and troubleshoot a systemd service; explain the dependency tree","Configure SSH key authentication; disable password auth; set up port forwarding","Monitor system resources (CPU, memory, disk, network) with command-line tools; identify the top resource consumer","Configure and manage a local firewall (iptables or nftables); allow and deny specific services","Automate a system administration task using Ansible; run on 3+ hosts without errors","Harden a Linux system to CIS Benchmark Level 1; document every setting and the security rationale","Administer a Linux environment with 10+ users, multiple services, and automated backups; no downtime for 30 days"],
