   "Batch errands and supply runs to minimize wasted trips; never run out of critical household items",
   "Plan and execute a domestic travel arrangement (flights, transport, lodging) independently and efficiently",
   "Move to a new apartment or barracks room with no lost or damaged items and all utilities/admin transferred",
   "Manage logistical complexity during an academic or training surge: food, gear, schedule, and supplies all maintained",
   "Execute a full PCS-style move (packing, transport, in-processing, household goods) with no administrative gaps",
   "Support another person's major transition (move, deployment prep, graduation) by applying your logistics systems",
